j.exceptions.ExceptionFactory\"\nmetadata/com.mysql/mysql-connector-j/8.0.31/reachability-metadata.json:105:      \"type\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.WrongArgumentException\",\nmetadata/io.undertow/undertow-parser-generator/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Undertow Parser Generator is an annotation processor that generates Undertow's HTTP parser classes. It supports build-time parser code generation for the Undertow web server.\",\nmetadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core-grpc/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"google-cloud-core-grpc provides shared gRPC transport infrastructure for Google Cloud Java client libraries. It includes transport options, shared resource management, and base exception handling used by gRPC-based Google Cloud clients.\",\nmetadata/io.undertow/undertow-core/2.2.19.Final/reachability-metadata.json:79:      \"type\": \"io.undertow.server.protocol.http.HttpRequestParser$$generated\",\nmetadata/com.google.cloud/proto-google-cloud-firestore-bundle-v1/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"This artifact provides generated Java Protocol Buffer classes and proto definitions for Google Cloud Firestore bundle messages. It models bundle metadata, named queries, bundled queries, and bundled document metadata used when serializing or consuming Firestore bundle data.\",\nmetadata/io.undertow/undertow-core/2.3.0.Final/reachability-metadata.json:136:          \"name\": \"errorCount\"\nmetadata/io.undertow/undertow-core/2.3.0.Final/reachability-metadata.json:237:      \"type\": \"io.undertow.server.protocol.http.HttpRequestParser$$generated\",\nmetadata/com.github.curious-odd-man/rgxgen/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"RgxGen generates strings that match a supplied regular expression pattern. It also supports iterating through unique matching strings and generating strings that do not match the pattern.\",\nmetadata/org.jboss.spec.javax.transaction/jboss-transaction-api_1.2_spec/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"This library provides the Java Transaction API 1.2 interfaces and annotations under javax.transaction for application-managed and container-managed transaction coordination. It supplies the standard exception types and contracts such as UserTransaction, TransactionManager, Transaction, Transactional, and TransactionSynchronizationRegistry used by Java EE runtimes and applications.\",\nmetadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ASM Debug All is the all-in-one debug build of ASM 5.0.1, a Java bytecode manipulation framework for reading, writing, and transforming class files. It bundles the ASM core, tree, commons, util, analysis, XML, and related debug-enabled components so tools can inspect, trace, analyze, and generate Java bytecode from one artifact.\",\nmetadata/org.atteo.classindex/classindex/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ClassIndex is a Java annotation processor and runtime API that builds indexes of annotated classes, subclasses, implementors, and package classes at compile time. Applications can query those generated indexes at runtime to avoid slower classpath scanning while remaining compatible with standard Java mechanisms such as ServiceLoader.\",\nmetadata/app.cash.sqldelight/runtime-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"SQLDelight Runtime JVM provides the Kotlin runtime APIs used by generated SQLDelight database code on the JVM. It includes query, transaction, driver, schema, cursor, and logging interfaces that generated code uses to execute SQL and map results.\",\nmetadata/app.cash.sqldelight/sqlite-driver/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"SQLDelight SQLite Driver provides a JVM SQLDelight SqlDriver implementation backed by SQLite through JDBC. It lets SQLDelight-generated Kotlin database code open SQLite connections, run statements, and manage transactions on the standard JVM.\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate/hibernate-jpamodelgen/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Hibernate JPAMetaModelGen is an annotation processor that generates JPA static metamodel classes from annotated entity classes. It supports type-safe Criteria API queries by producing canonical model classes during Java compilation.\",\nmetadata/app.cash.sqldelight/jdbc-driver/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"SQLDelight JDBC Driver provides a JVM SqlDriver implementation backed by JDBC connections for SQLDelight-generated Kotlin database code. It maps JDBC ResultSet and PreparedStatement operations into SQLDelight cursor, statement, transaction, and connection APIs so applications can use JDBC-accessible databases.\",\nmetadata/org.ow2.asm/asm/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"ASM is a small and fast Java bytecode manipulation framework for reading, writing, and transforming Java class files. The core asm artifact provides the event-based visitor API used to generate bytecode, inspect classes, and implement tools such as compilers, profilers, and code generators.\",\nmetadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-util/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ASM Util provides utility classes and command-line-oriented tools for ASM's Java bytecode manipulation framework, including bytecode checking, tracing, textification, and ASMifier generation. It helps developers inspect compiled classes and generate ASM visitor code that reproduces equivalent bytecode structures.\",\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:68:        \"typeReached\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.ExceptionFactory\"\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:70:      \"type\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.CJCommunicationsException\",\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:75:        \"typeReached\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.ExceptionFactory\"\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:77:      \"type\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.InvalidConnectionAttributeException\",\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:84:      \"type\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.RSAException\",\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:89:        \"typeReached\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.ExceptionFactory\"\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:91:      \"type\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.UnableToConnectException\",\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:96:        \"typeReached\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.ExceptionFactory\"\nmetadata/mysql/mysql-connector-java/8.0.29/reachability-metadata.json:98:      \"type\": \"com.mysql.cj.exceptions.WrongArgumentException\",\nmetadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta Annotations defines standard Java annotations for common semantic concepts used across Jakarta EE and related Java technologies. This artifact provides the version 3.0.0 API types in the jakarta.annotation package, including lifecycle, security, resource, nullability, priority, and generated-code annotations.\",\nmetadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta Annotations defines standard Java annotations for common semantic concepts used across Jakarta EE and related Java technologies. This artifact provides the version 2.1.0 API types in the jakarta.annotation package, including lifecycle, security, resource, and generated-code annotations.\",\nmetadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:38:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta Annotations defines standard Java annotations for common semantic concepts used across Jakarta EE and other Java technologies. This artifact provides the version 2.0.0 API types in the `jakarta.annotation` package, including lifecycle, security, resource, and generated-code annotations.\",\nmetadata/jakarta.annotation/jakarta.annotation-api/index.json:52:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta Annotations defines a standard set of common Java annotations that support declarative programming across Java technologies. This artifact provides the 1.3.3 API types in the `javax.annotation` package, including lifecycle, resource, and generated-code annotations.\",\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-pkitesting/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Netty PKITesting provides test support utilities for building X.509 certificates, certificate bundles, and certificate revocation data. It is used by Netty's TLS and PKI-related tests to generate and serve certificate material without relying on external infrastructure.\",\nmetadata/com.google.flatbuffers/flatbuffers-java/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"FlatBuffers Java is the Java runtime API for Google's FlatBuffers serialization format, which stores structured data in compact binary buffers that can be read without unpacking. It provides builders, table/vector accessors, and FlexBuffers support used by generated Java code to create and inspect FlatBuffer messages.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-format-structures/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Parquet Format Structures provides Java classes used by parquet-mr to work with the parquet-format Thrift structures. It packages generated model code for Parquet schema and metadata structures so Parquet Java components can read and write the format consistently.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-format-structures/index.json:36:    \"description\" : \"Apache Parquet Format Structures provides Java classes used by parquet-mr to work with the parquet-format Thrift structures. It packages generated model code for Parquet schema and metadata structures so Parquet Java components can read and write the format consistently.\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/7.3.0.Final/reachability-metadata.json:6725:          \"name\" : \"generatedBy\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-envers/6.1.1.Final/reachability-metadata.json:450:        \"typeReached\": \"org.hibernate.envers.exception.RevisionDoesNotExistException\"\nmetadata/org.apache.geronimo.specs/geronimo-annotation_1.3_spec/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Geronimo Annotation Spec 1.3 provides the JSR-250 Common Annotations 1.3 API in the javax.annotation packages. It supplies standard annotations for lifecycle callbacks, resource injection metadata, security roles, generated-code markers, priorities, and SQL data source declarations.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.geronimo.specs/geronimo-annotation_1.1_spec/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"This artifact provides Apache Geronimo's implementation of the JSR-250 Common Annotations 1.1 API in the javax.annotation packages. It supplies annotation types and annotation processing contracts used by Java EE components, dependency injection, security roles, lifecycle callbacks, generated code markers, and data source declarations.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.geronimo.specs/geronimo-jta_1.1_spec/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"This artifact provides Apache Geronimo's Java Transaction API (JTA) 1.1 specification classes in the javax.transaction and javax.transaction.xa packages. It supplies the standard transaction contracts, status constants, exceptions, synchronization callbacks, and XA resource types used by transaction managers and Java EE applications.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/unroll-annotation_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"unroll-annotation_3 provides the Scala 3 annotation class for Li Haoyi's Unroll compiler plugin. The annotation marks methods, classes, constructors, and case classes whose default parameters should have telescoping forwarders generated to preserve binary compatibility.\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/7.0.0.Final/reachability-metadata.json:6706:          \"name\": \"generatedBy\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/8.0.0.Alpha1/reachability-metadata.json:6874:          \"name\": \"generatedBy\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/fastparse_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"FastParse is a Scala parser-combinator library for building efficient parsers for structured text such as programming languages, data formats, and domain-specific languages. It provides composable parsing primitives, error reporting, and cross-platform support that let applications define readable parsers directly in Scala code.\",\nmetadata/io.javaslang/javaslang-match/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Javaslang Match provides annotations and an annotation processor that generate support code for structural pattern matching in Java. It is part of the Javaslang functional programming library and helps Java applications express match-style control flow with generated pattern helpers.\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/7.1.0.Final/reachability-metadata.json:6706:          \"name\": \"generatedBy\",\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/NativeTestCompileInvocationTask.java:26:    protected String errorMessageFor(String coordinates, int exitCode) {\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/NativeTestCompileInvocationTask.java:27:        return \"Native test compilation failed\";\nmetadata/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Selenium API provides the core Java interfaces and exceptions used by Selenium WebDriver to automate browsers. It defines browser automation contracts such as WebDriver, WebElement, By, capabilities, and related support types that client libraries and drivers implement.\",\nmetadata/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-api/index.json:25:    \"description\" : \"Selenium API provides the core Java interfaces and exceptions used by Selenium WebDriver to automate browsers. It defines browser automation contracts such as WebDriver, WebElement, By, capabilities, and related support types that client libraries and drivers implement.\",\nmetadata/io.smallrye.classfile/jdk-classfile-backport/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"JDK Classfile API Backport provides a Java 17-compatible backport of the JDK Classfile API from JDK 21 and later. It lets JVM applications parse, inspect, transform, and generate Java class files through the io.smallrye.classfile API.\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/7.2.0.Final/reachability-metadata.json:6721:          \"name\": \"generatedBy\",\nmetadata/io.zipkin.reporter2/zipkin-reporter/index.json:50:    \"description\" : \"Zipkin Reporter is the core Java library for asynchronously reporting Zipkin spans to pluggable senders. It provides buffering, batching, metrics hooks, and error handling used by transport-specific Zipkin reporter modules.\",\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-services/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"grpc-services provides Java implementations and generated APIs for standard gRPC services such as health checking, reflection, channelz, and binary logging. It is used by gRPC Java servers and clients to expose or consume operational service endpoints alongside application RPC services.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.arrow/arrow-format/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Arrow Format provides generated Java classes for Apache Arrow IPC FlatBuffer metadata definitions. It lets Java applications work with the schema, record batch, dictionary batch, and message structures used by Arrow's columnar interchange format.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.arrow/arrow-format/index.json:33:    \"description\" : \"Apache Arrow Format provides generated Java classes for the Apache Arrow IPC FlatBuffer metadata definitions. It lets Java applications work with the schema, record batch, dictionary batch, and message structures used by Arrow's columnar interchange format.\",\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-rls/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"grpc-rls provides the gRPC Java Route Lookup Service load-balancing plugin. It lets gRPC clients use route lookup configuration and generated RLS service types to choose routing targets for RPCs.\",\nmetadata/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/reachability-metadata.json:751:      \"glob\" : \"org_aspectj/aspectjweaver/generated/LegacyConcreteAspect.class\"\nmetadata/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/reachability-metadata.json:757:      \"glob\" : \"org_aspectj/aspectjweaver/generated/LegacyConcreteAspect.class\"\nmetadata/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/reachability-metadata.json:763:      \"glob\" : \"org_aspectj/aspectjweaver/generated/LoadTimeConcreteAspect.class\"\nmetadata/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/reachability-metadata.json:769:      \"glob\" : \"org_aspectj/aspectjweaver/generated/LoadTimeConcreteAspect.class\"\nmetadata/javax.jcr/jcr/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Defines the Java Content Repository (JCR) 1.0 API for accessing content repositories independently of a specific implementation. It provides the standard javax.jcr interfaces, classes, and exceptions for sessions, workspaces, nodes, properties, queries, observation, locking, and versioning.\",\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-value-registry/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Quarkus Value Registry provides a low-level API for registering and retrieving immutable runtime values generated by Quarkus or its extensions, such as application state that is only known at startup. It keeps those values outside the configuration system and lets unrelated services share runtime information through typed keys without introducing dependency cycles or exposing internal APIs.\",\nmetadata/com.google.api/gax/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"GAX (Google API Extensions) for Java provides core abstractions used by Google Java client libraries, including call settings, retry and polling behavior, batching, paging, operations, and credential provider utilities. It supplies transport-neutral support code that generated Google API clients use to make API calls consistently across gRPC and HTTP/JSON transports.\",\nmetadata/com.google.api/gax-httpjson/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"GAX HTTP JSON provides the HTTP/JSON transport layer for Google API Extensions for Java, including request execution, JSON transcoding, response parsing, and channel/provider support. It is used by generated Google Java clients to call Google APIs over HTTP/JSON while sharing the common GAX abstractions for settings, credentials, retries, and operations.\",\nmetadata/com.github.scopt/scopt_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"scopt is a command-line options parsing library for Scala applications. It provides parser APIs for defining options, commands, validation, and generated usage or help output.\",\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-runner/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Quarkus Bootstrap Runner provides production runtime bootstrap classes, entry points, class loaders, resource access, and logging setup for Quarkus applications packaged with the runner architecture. It is used by generated Quarkus applications to load application classes and resources at runtime while keeping the bootstrap layer minimal and parent-first dependency behavior controlled.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.maven/maven-api-meta/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Maven API Meta provides the annotation types used by Maven 4's immutable API, including nullability, threading, provider, consumer, generated, and experimental markers. These annotations help Maven APIs and integrations communicate intended usage contracts without adding runtime behavior.\",\nmetadata/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-reporting/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"JUnit Platform Reporting provides listeners and XML writers for legacy and Open Test Reporting formats. It is used by JUnit Platform launchers and native test integrations to generate test execution reports.\",\nmetadata/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-placeholders/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/xmlunit/xmlunit-placeholders/$version$/xmlunit-placeholders-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-placeholders/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/xmlunit/xmlunit-placeholders/$version$/xmlunit-placeholders-$version$-tests.jar\",\